         "id": "SECTION_introduction",
         "text": [
            {
               "text": "### Introduction\n\nWhen studying the equality between two quantities, we learned that when quantities are completely equal, subtracting one from the other yields a result equal to zero (<htcite0>).\n\nIn some situations, even if we do not have entirely equal objects, it is still possible to consider them as the same objects (<htcite1>).",
               "source": [
                  {
                     "type": 1,
                     "uuid": "aa6b052f-05ca-4979-a3a7-a4b7e70618ef",
                     "text": "History Tracers Team",
                     "page": "The Difference of Equals",
                     "date_time": {
                        "type": "gregory",
                        "year": "2025",
                        "month": "11",
                        "day": "30"
                     }
                  },
                  {
                     "type": 1,
                     "uuid": "a05ccb5a-182d-4321-8105-f30ee47edfc6",
                     "text": "History Tracers Team",
                     "page": "Equality Levels",
                     "date_time": {
                        "type": "gregory",
                        "year": "2024",
                        "month": "-1",
                        "day": "-1"
                     }
                  }
               ],
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "markdown",
               "PostMention": ""
            },
            {
               "text": "<p><center><div class=\"first_steps_reflection_parent\"><div class=\"first_steps_reflection question_mark\"><i class=\"fa-solid fa-brain\"></i></div><div class=\"first_steps_reflection\"><b>Reflection 1: Almost the Same</b><br /><br />Can we use subtraction to determine if two objects are similar?<br /><br />Could there be another operation that could help us obtain more details?</div></div></center></p>",
               "source": null,
